Introduction

NOIR is an eight-member boy group originally formed under LUK Factory. They debuted on April 9, 2018, with their first mini-album, Twenty's Noir. Initially consisting of nine members, the group has undergone significant changes in recent years, showcasing their resilience and dedication to their music and fans.

In 2024, it was revealed that members Junyong, Siheon, Hoyeon, Siha, Minhyuk, and Daewon had successfully terminated their contracts with LUK Factory following a legal battle. The members cited the agency's failure to provide necessary resources for their activities and unauthorized attempts to transfer their contracts to another agency. Despite these challenges, the group remains committed to their craft, continuing to grow as artists and performers.
